Berg n in Switzerland Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories A community in Switzerland has decided to ban tourists from taking photos at a popular tourist destination because it is &ldquo;too beautiful&rdquo; and any photos of it would induce unbearable envy.Berg&uuml;n looks like something out of a fairy tale and you have to go there in person to appreciate it, the locals say. The town has put up a sign warning tourists that they&rsquo;re not allowed to take photos, reports the Daily Star.The sign reads: &ldquo;Photographs of our picturesque landscape, shared on social media, can make others unhappy because they themselves cannot be here.&rdquo;The community voted to ban tourists from taking pictures as they want their visitors to &ldquo;take in the beauty of it without phones&rdquo;.Naturally, tourists have flouted the ban and have taken selfies next to the sign, and also still capture images of the stunning views. To be able to take photos, the city&rsquo;s mayor said there was a &ldquo;friendly special permit&rdquo; that allows photography within the city limits.The permit is free &ndash; all you need to do is ask. &ndash; The Mirror24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.